e salta is ranked by fraser institute as one of the most favorable jurisdictions in central and south america for exploration the region is home to two producing lithium mines—orocobre’s olaroz and fmc’s salar de hombre muerto advantage lithium says it’s ready to do the real work of exploring and developing at its jv lithium properties and management has a longterm goal of taking the company to producer status a sixhole program is planned for q  at the company’s flagship clayton ne project “with a drill program soon to start at our clayton ne project in nevada a recent agreement to acquire four exciting earlystage projects in mexico and now this more advanced project next to orocobre’s large and shallow resource at salar de salinas grandes we are closer to fulfilling our goal as a leading junior in the lithium space” commented david sidoo president and ceo of advantage lithium the company is led by a group of awardwinning company builders with a track record of success in creating maximum shareholder value including fission uranium founder and ceo dev randhawa american oil  gas founder and significant shareholder david sidoo and fission uranium president coo and chief geologist ross mcelroy in august  advantage lithium announced the closing of a financing with gross proceeds of  million and another round of financing was announced in early september for up to an additional  million investment highlights  lithium brine projects  drillready in the clayton valley and lida valley region proximal to north america’s only producing lithium brine operation—albermarle’s silver peak mine clayton ne border only  meters from several silver peak production wells drilling at clayton ne to begin in q  brine deposits typically have lower exploration and operating costs than hard rock deposits advantage lithium jv is the only lithium exploration company with access to water rights in the clayton valley basin where the state of nevada has overappropriated water rights four lithium br