oximately  m targeting sand and halite units identified at cauchari and olaroz it is estimated that  weeks will be required to drill each hole and install a well to the required depth inhole geophysical profiling and geological logging will provide the basis for installing screen intervals in the wells other activities will sequentially follow completion and cleaning of the wells once clean brine sampling will be undertaken in the wells at different depth intervals using packer equipment to establish the distribution of lithium throughout each well as detailed sampling will follow well installation brine analytical results are likely to become available approximately  weeks after the initiation of each hole pump testing will then be undertaken following completion of depth sampling with variable and fixed rate flow tests planned to assess the production capacity and lithium grade of each well the wells will be installed so they can be used for future brine production additional rotary andor diamond drill holes will be added as justified by initial results as we proceed towards engineering studies the holes to be drilled are located immediately east and west of properties where lithium americas corp lac previously defined a large lithium brine resource in an ni report dated th july  figure  shows the location of the advantage lithium exploration target areas relative to the neighboring resource figure  location of the phase  drill holes relative to previous drilling figure  rig drilling hole cau in the cauchari northwestern properties and figure  the location of the cauchari drilling areas relative to the lithium americas corp lithium resource  an exploration target is not a mineral resource the potential quantity and grade of the exploration target is conceptual in nature and there has been insufficient exploration to define a mineral resource in the volume where the exploration target is outlined it is uncertain if further exploration drilling will result in the determination of a mineral resource in this volume the technical information in this news release has reviewed and approved on behalf of the company by murray brooker maig rpgeo a qualified person as defined in ni  about advantage lithium corp advantage lithium corp is a resource company specializing in the strategic acquisition exploration and development of lithium properties and is headquartered in vancouver british columbia the common shares of the company are listed on the tsx venture exchange tsx ventureaal and the company is also traded on the otcqx best market in the us otcqx avlif the company has acquired a  interest in five projects in argentina and up to a  interest in a sixth called cauchari cauchari is located just  km south of orocobres flagship olaroz lithium facility the company is also earning an interest from nevada sunrise gold corp in a portfolio of five lithium brine projects in the clayton and lida valley regions of nevada usa including  in clayton ne further information about the company can be found at wwwadvantagelithiumcom more mining news cordoba minerals announces significant southern extension to alacran coppergold deposit in colombia gt gold drills new discovery at saddle south intercepts  gt au over  metres nulegacy gold discovers new zone at iceberg deposit drills  meters of  gt gold marathon gold drills  gt au over  meters at valentine lake camp uranium energy corp completes  drill holes at burke hollow isr project extends  campaign to september emx royalty announces ig copper drill results intersects  meters averaging  copper equivalent at malmyzh porphyry project roxgold produces  ounces of gold at yaramoko in q  remains on track to achieve upper end of annual production guidance zinc one resources enters into surface access agreement with comunidad campesina de yambrasbamba on bongara zincoxide project victoria gold drills m of  gt au at eagle west dublin gulch yukon denison mines drills  metres of  euo as gryphon exploration contin